	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />One of the nbasic games didn't properly abide by VRAM write rules. It would write data to $2007 during rendering and mess up the display if I recall. It was the Sack of Flour game. <br /><br />Honestly 6502 ASM isn't that daunting. But if it is too much for you then using the resources about writing NES games in C is the best option. That NBASIC isn't worth it.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
